ARM, BMW, Deutsche Boerse, HSBC, Icade: European Equity Preview

-- B y   K a i t l y n   K i e r n a n
-- 
2011-10-20T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/arm-bmw-deutsche-boerse-hsbc-icade-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index gained 0.6 percent to 236.71.
The Stoxx 50 Index rose 0.7 percent to 2,259.53. The Euro Stoxx
50 Index, a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
advanced 1 percent to 2,330.08.  ARM Holdings Plc (ARM)  : The owner of chip technology
used in Apple Inc. (AAPL US) iPhones introduced a new design for
semiconductors to be used in low-end smartphones and devices as
it seeks to expand in new markets. The shares slid 1.9 percent
to 580.50 pence.  Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  : The German carmaker
that is poised to become the best-selling luxury brand in the
U.S. this year said it can can keep the spot in 2012’s first
quarter as it introduces its redesigned 3-Series sedan. The
shares lost 0.1 percent to 55.01 euros.  Deutsche Boerse AG (DB1)  (DB1 GY): The Frankfurt Stock Exchange
owner that agreed to buy NYSE Euronext to create the world’s
biggest bourse operator beat profit and sales estimates after a
rout in equities spurred a surge in third-quarter trading. The
shares fell 0.1 percent to 41.04 euros.  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  : Europe’s biggest bank is
interested in buying  Turkey ’s Denizbank from  Dexia SA (DEXB)  ,
the first lender to founder with the European debt crisis, two
people with knowledge of the process said. HSBC gained 0.4
percent to 522.50 pence. Dexia rose 1.7 percent to 61 euro
cents.  Icade (ICAD)  : The commercial property arm of  France ’s
Caisse des Depots et Consignations reported third-quarter
revenue rose 13 percent of 348.6 million euros. The shares
advanced 0.3 percent to 64.52 euros.  Zardoya Otis SA (ZOT)  : The Spanish elevator unit of
 United Technologies Corp. (UTX)   was boosted to “hold” from
“underweight” at Banco Santander SA. The shares climbed 1.4
percent to 9.63 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
